{
  "texts": [
    "One kind looks like an infinity sign, resembling a Bernoulli lemniscate (which is given in polar coordinates by r 2 = cos(2φ)).",
    "This kind occurs between two bowls, or between two hills.",
    "The other kind of saddle-point contours resembles a limaçon trisectrix (r = 1 -2 cos φ in polar coordinates), which corresponds to a hill within a bowl.",
    "The lens in Fig. 6 is an elliptical mass distribution (a commonly-used form called a PIEMD -see Appendix A).",
    "Each panel shows τ (θ, β) for a different β."
  ]
}